Name: malignant ovarian surface epithelial-stromal neoplasm
Definition: An ovary epithelial cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial and stromal tissue and arises from the surface epithelium of the ovary.

Name: ovarian squamous cell neoplasm
Definition: An ovary epithelial cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

Name: ovarian mucinous neoplasm
Definition: An ovary epithelial cancer that is characterized by the presence of mucin.

Name: ovarian papillary neoplasm
Definition: An ovary epithelial cancer that is characterized by the presence of finger-like projections on histology.

Name: familiar ovarian carcinoma
Definition: A mixed epithelial tumor of ovary that is cancerous.
Synonym: pediatric carcinoma of the Liver cell

Name: Krukenberg carcinoma
Definition: An ovary epithelial cancer that is a metastatic signet-ring cell carcinoma
